  "text": "Use of long-wave infrared-absorbing plastic film for greenhouse covering reduces nighttime heat loss and thus the opportunity for condensation on plant surfaces, reducing Botrytis disease on tomatoes [CITATION_1] . Films that restrict UV light penetration also reduce Botrytis sporulation [CITATION_2] .",
